gameRecap.title: Game Recap: Kings 124, Warriors 123
gameRecap.excerpt: Malik Monk made a go-ahead jumper with 7.4 seconds left followed by a Stephen Curry missed 3PT at the buzzer as the Kings defeated the Warriors, 124-123. DeAaron Fox led Sacramento with 29 points, 10 rebounds, and seven assists as Kevin Huerter (21 points, nine rebounds, five assists) and Malik Monk (21 points) totaled 42 points. Stephen Curry (29 points, 10 rebounds, six assists) and Andrew Wiggins (20 points, nine rebounds) totaled 58 points to lead Golden State as Klay Thompson added 20 points and 11 rebounds. The Kings move to 4-0 in West C play and 10-6 on year as the Warriors move to 2-2 in West C play and 8-10 on the year.
